Parents are demanding an urgent review of the hair policy at a Cape Town school. CAPE TOWN - Parents are demanding an urgent review of the hair policy at a Cape Town school. Pupils at Malibu High in Blue Downs claim they've been discriminated against for wearing afros. READ: Gauteng high school embroiled in natural hair scandal  The Western Cape Education Department says the girls violated the school's restrictions on certain hairstyles. READ: School rules: give them a hint with hair The department says it's encouraged school governing bodies to update policies, and get pupils involved. Some concerned parents at Malibu High, however, want the school governing body to change the policy now. READ: School entangled in hair discrimination loses case It's not the first time a school's hair rules have come under the spotlight. In 2016, hundreds of pupils protested at Sans Souci Girls' High in Cape Town.